<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tornado Ravages South Dakota Town </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, May 31 (Xinhua) -- A tornado destroyed much of
Spencer, a small town in South Dakota, during the night, killing
at least five people and injuring scores.
</P>
<P>
The twister late Saturday may have been one-quarter of a mile
wide, witnesses said.
</P>
<P>
Apartment buildings, houses, the bank, churches, the post
office and other buildings were damaged, reports said.
</P>
<P>
Governor Bill Janklow activated the National Guard, and about
100 prison inmates also were sent to help look for people trapped
or injured.
</P>
<P>
"The entire town is destroyed, there are deceased people and a
lot of injured people," The Associated Press quoted the governor
as saying.
</P>
<P>
The television station reported that 150 people were injured.
</P>
<P>
Violent thunderstorms also struck parts of Minnesota, Wisconsin
and Michigan during the night, and utilities said hundreds of
thousands of customers were without power Sunday.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
