<DOCNO> XIE19980601.0005 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zambian Government Urged to Quicken Copper Mines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, May 31 (Xinhua) -- The Zambia Association of
Manufacturers (ZAM) Sunday urged the Zambian government to
quicken privatization of the Zambia Consolidated Copper Mines
(ZCCM), the Zambia News Agency (ZANA) said.
</P>
<P>
ZAM even called on the government to sell some mines at a
give-away price to save the country's economy from collapse.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with ZANA in Lusaka, ZAM Chairman Mark
O'Donnell said that in view of an apparent shortage of buyers for
Nchanga and Nkana mines, the largest mines in Zambia, they should
be sold at any price as long as the country could benefit from
the long-term investment.
</P>
<P>
"The government's offer should not just be cash on the table
but what the new investment would do to the country," said
O'Donnell.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the government should not insist on selling the
mines at higher prices because even at much lower offer, the
economy could benefit as the new capital investment could boost
production and employment in the long-run.
</P>
<P>
Any further delay in the privatization of ZCCM, a major
foreign exchange earner for Zambia, could spell doom for the
country's economy, he said.
</P>
<P>
The ZAM chairman pointed out that a number of companies whose
sustainability depends on ZCCM are already struggling financially
and they could collapse when ZCCM grinds to a halt.
</P>
<P>
He urged the government to look for a reputable and
world-class business partner to buy the mines at low concessions
for the sake of recapitalizing ZCCM and turning the mining
conglomerate into a viable economic activity.
</P>
<P>
The negotiations to privatize Nchanga and Nkana mines are
undergoing between the Zambia government and the Kafue
consortium, an international company.
</P>
<P>
But Zambian President Frederick Chiluba said that the Zambian
government will never sell the mines at a give-away price.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
