<BODY>
<HEADLINE> India Calls For Negotiations On Nuclear Weapons </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, May 31 (Xinhua) -- After triggering a nuclear arms
race in South Asia by detonating five nuclear devices, India on
Sunday proposed that all nuclear weapons states and the
international community open negotiations for a nuclear weapons
convention.
</P>
<P>
A statement issued this evening by the Ministry of External
Affairs said that the convention is necessary to deal with these
weapons in a global non-discriminatory framework as the other two
weapons of mass destruction had been through the biological
weapons convention and the chemical weapons convention.
</P>
<P>
In the statement, India expressed its displeasure with the
United Nations Security Council statement for what it called
"references against New Dehli." The Security Council in a
statement on Saturday urged India and Pakistan to call a
moratorium on nuclear testing and sign the Comprehensive Test Ban
Treaty. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
