<HEADLINE> South Ossetian Vice-Premier Assassinated </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, May 31 (Xinhua) -- A ranking official of Georgia's
South Ossetia region was killed by unidentified gunmen on Sunday
in downtown Vladiskavkaz, North Ossetia, Itar-Tass reported.
</P>
<P>
Valery Khubulov, deputy head of the South Ossentian government,
was known in the Caucasus for his peace-making efforts. He was
shot dead while riding a car with a companion. The assasins then
blasted the car to cover up traces, Itar-Tass said.
</P>
<P>
The companion was seriously injured.
</P>
<P>
Mobile units of the Interior Ministry of North Ossentia, which
is inside Russia, are investigating the case, the news agency
said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
