<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-31 17:38 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> One Lebanese Civilian Killed by Israeli Missile </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Israeli troops fired a missile near
a village in south Lebanon, killing a Lebanese civilian and
wounding another Sunday afternoon, Lebanese National News Agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
The missile crashed on the edge of the Arbsalim village, north
of the Israeli occupied security zone, hitting the two shepherds,
the agency said.
</P>
<P>
One of them died after being taken to the hospital in the
southern port city of Sida, it said, adding that a number of their
herds were also killed during the Israeli shelling.
</P>
<P>
The attack came just hours after the Iranian-backed Hezbollah,
or Party of God, launched a series of offensives at Israeli
positions in the zone.
</P>
<P>
The fresh casualty has brought the number of Lebanese civilians
killed and wounded in clashes between Hezbollah and Israeli troops
to 10 and 44 respectively since the beginning of this year.
</P>
<P>
Israel has been occupying a 1,200-square-kilometer border strip in
south Lebanon since 1985 with the claimed aims of protecting its
northern areas from guerrilla cross border attacks.
</P>
<P>
Hezbollah has since spearheaded a guerrilla war to try to drive
1,200 Israeli troops and their Lebanese militia allies out of the
occupied zone. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
