<HEADLINE> H.K. Launches Health Education Program for Students </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Associated by the Education
Department, Hong Kong's Provisional Urban Council launched here on
Monday a new campaign to let school students know more about
environmental hygiene.
</P>
<P>
The "Know More about Environmental Hygiene Facilities and Life
Skill Training Camp" will invite Secondary Two to Four school
students in the "New Territories" and outlying islands to gain
more knowledge on their environmental hygiene facilities. The
free-of-charge event will also help them take part in a
challenging life skill training camp during this summer holiday.
</P>
<P>
The new health education program aimed at encouraging students
to make good use of their environmental hygiene facilities and
service, and then disseminate the message to their schoolmates,
friends and family members.
</P>
<P>
Entrants had to attend a quiz on July 2 to test their knowledge
on food and environmental hygiene as well as the environmental
hygiene facilities and services provided by the Council, according
to a spokesman for the Health Education Unit of the Regional
Services Department (RSD).
</P>
<P>
Those who have completed the program will be issued a
Certificate of Award and will have an opportunity to take part in
the Food Hygiene Carnival set for February next year and other
education activities.
</P>
<P>
"It is expected that through visits and training, participating
students will be more aware of the importance of environmental
hygiene, be able to understand more about themselves and have
their life skills further enhanced," the spokesman added. 
</P>
