<HEADLINE> ASEAN Insurance Training Fund Launched </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 1 (Xinhua) -- The ASEAN Insurance Training
Fund (AITF) was launched here Monday to offer annual scholarship
to ASEAN students to study insurance professional courses in
Malaysia on a full-time basis.
</P>
<P>
The AITF, mooted by Malaysian government at the first ASEAN
finance ministers meeting last year, amounts to 6 million ringgit
(1.53 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The Malaysian government has contributed half of the amount to
the fund while the Malaysian insurance industry has contributed
the rest half.
</P>
<P>
The fund will provide a total of 75 scholarships to qualified
insurance personnel in ASEAN to be trained over the next five
years, Malaysia's Bank Negara (Central Bank) Governor Ahmad
Mohamed Don said at the launching.
</P>
<P>
The Malaysian Insurance Institute (MII), the fund manager of
the AITF, will provide the facilities to conduct two courses --
Diploma in Insurance or Diploma in Risk Management as well as the
MII Associateship technical training programs.
</P>
<P>
Besides Malaysia, ASEAN also groups Brunei, Indonesia, Laos,
Myanmar, the Philippines, Singapore, Thailand and Vietnam.
</P>
</TEXT>
