<HEADLINE> HKSAR's Housing Authority to Promote Family Care For the Elderly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 1 (Xinhua) -- The Housing Authority (HA) of the
Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) government has
approved a series of measures to promote family care for the
elderly by encouraging public housing applicants to live with
elderly members.
</P>
<P>
The HA's Rental Housing Committee (RHC) approved here on Monday
to further improve the existing two priority schemes which
encourage families on the Waiting List to take care of their
elderly members.
</P>
<P>
HA has also proposed giving priorities in the future to
families with elderly in their applying for Home Ownership
Scheme/Private Sector Participation Scheme (HOS/PSPS) and Home
Purchase Loan Scheme (HPLS).
</P>
<P>
RHC Chairman Chan Kam-man said that the Housing Department (HD)
had been working closely with the Elderly Commission in
contributing to the government's Strategic Policy Objective on
Elderly Services. "To address the housing needs of an increasing
elderly population, we have to take proactive and timely steps to
put in place a coherent housing policy to promote family care for
the elderly," he said.
</P>
<P>
The HA currently has two elderly priority schemes -- the
Families with Elderly Persons Priority Scheme (FEP) and the
Special Scheme for Families with Elderly Persons (NFEP).
</P>
<P>
The HA has also proposed to accord priority to families
applying for HOS/PSPS and with elderly members. It is also
proposed to accord priority to eligible HPLS applicants living
with elderly members. 
</P>
</TEXT>
