<HEADLINE> Karachi Stock Exchange Index Drops Below 1000-Level </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 1 (Xinhua) -- The Karachi Stock Exchange
(KSE)-100 Index plunged Monday to an all-time record low as the
bourse reacted strongly to last week's nuclear tests by Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
The KSE-100 index dropped 128.76 points drastically Monday to
close at 911.44 against last Thursday's close of 1040.20 points.
</P>
<P>
Analysts say that the reason for Monday's crash was mainly the
decision by the government to freeze foreign currency accounts.
</P>
<P>
"Despite the fact that these restrictions were lifted for
foreign investors who were trading in the stock exchange, the
overall impact has been very negative and foreigners are taking
out their money when they can," they say.
</P>
<P>
Soon after a decision was taken Monday morning to re-open the
bourse, the market saw some heavy selling.
</P>
<P>
The KSE index continued its decline throughout the day and
finally closed at a record all-time low. After the close, the
board of the KSE went into a meeting to decide what course of
action to adopt on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
A total volume of 52.98 million shares were traded on Monday
against 78.6 million shares traded in the previous trading day.
The market was closed on Friday on account of bank holiday.
</P>
<P>
There were 10 gainers and 95 losers Monday.
</P>
<P>
Traders expected the market to continue its downward slide on
Tuesday in the absence of any positive news or indicators.
</P>
</TEXT>
