<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Killing, Abduction Continue in Somali Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Killing and abduction activities
by freelance gangs escalated Monday in the Somali capital
as part of the on-going violence and lawlessness in the country.
</P>
<P>
Four people were killed and five others wounded when
unidentified gunmen opened fire indiscriminately on a public
transport bus in south Mogadishu early Monday morning.
</P>
<P>
According to eyewitnesses, the bus, the first from the animal
market after the morning prayers, had been awaited by several
gunmen at Ali Kamin junction where the bus wound to drop some of
its passengers.
</P>
<P>
The attack is said to be a retaliatory move taken by armed
militiamen annoyed by a similar bus theft in south Mogadishu a
few days ago by members of the sub-clansmen of the owner of the
attacked bus.
</P>
<P>
The bodyguard of the bus managed to return fire and jumped
over the bus to defend it from the offenders until the neighbors
came out to help him.
</P>
<P>
The driver and conductor of the bus were also seriously
wounded in the incident. All those injured were rushed to a
nearby voluntary hospital for treatment. The ambush has been one
of the bloodiest vehicle-jacking attempt in recent weeks in
Mogadishu.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Sheikh Omar Nur Omar (Awdhegle), a local aid worker
serving the French aid agency, Action Contra Le Faim (ACF), has
been abducted by unidentified gunmen in south Mogadishu on
Saturday. Local staff members of ACF said he was taken away to
an unidentified locality in the capital.
</P>
<P>
The ACF aid workers said they are still looking for him trying
to establish a string of information reaching for Sheikh Omar
Awdhegle who had been in charge of the financial affairs of the
agency in Mogadishu. The reason for the abduction is not known
to anyone, however, close friends attributed the abduction to a
contract dispute.
</P>
<P>
This is the second time that Sheikh Omar Awdhegle is abducted
by Somali gunmen. On September 11, he was kidnappe by gunmen
and released two days later on what the agency termed as
non-conditional release.
</P>
<P>
The abduction of the aid worker came at a time when the main
faction leaders of the capital are calling for the return of the
international expatriates back to Mogadishu following their
evacuation for safety after 10 aid workers of the International
Committee of the Red Cross (ICRC) were kidnapped in north
Mogadishu in mid April.
</P>
<P>
The faction leaders are becoming powerless in dealing with the
growing insecurity in the capital.
</P>
<P>
The aid worker's abduction is also taking place at a time when
serious cholera outbreak is further spreading in the Somali
capital and its surrounding areas as well as many other parts of
the country.
</P>
<P>
ACF is one of the five member team of the cholera task force
in collaboration with Mogadishu's joint health authority. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
