Most heads of state and governments from the 113-member
organization of developing countries will attend the summit in Durban
in early September. South Africa takes over the chair of the movement
from Columbia at the meeting.
</P>
<P>
As new Non-Aligned Movement chairman, President Nelson Mandela is
expected to make a keynote speech on development and north-south
issues at the summit. 
