<HEADLINE> Chinese Defense Minister Holds Talks With Belorussian Counterpart </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Defense Minister General
Chi Haotian, in talks with his Belorussian counterpart General
Alexander Chumakov here today, said that China is satisfied with
the current friendly cooperation between the two armed forces.
</P>
<P>
This is Chumakov's first visit to China. Chi, who is also
vice-chairman of the Central Military Commission and a state
councillor, expressed his belief that this visit will push the
friendly and cooperative ties between the two armed forces to a
new height.
</P>
<P>
Chi said relations between China and Belarus have developed
rapidly in recent years, and the two countries have only common
interests, without conflicts of fundamental interests, and they
share a consensus on many international issues.
</P>
<P>
Chi expressed appreciation for Belarus' support for China on
the issues of human rights and Taiwan. He noted that the
development of bilateral friendly and cooperative relations in
various sectors is not only in the fundamental interests of the
two peoples but is conducive to peace and stability in Asia,
Europe and the world as a whole, as well as to the
multipolarization of the world.
</P>
<P>
Chi said relations between the two armed forces is increasingly
enhanced with the development of country-to-country relations, and
China has always taken a positive attitude toward developing
relations between the two armed forces
</P>
<P>
Chi said that China is ready to make concerted efforts with
Belarus to advance the multi-level and multi-sector friendly and
cooperative ties oriented toward the 21st century between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
With regard to the status of the Chinese People's Liberation
Army (PLA), Chi noted that PLA is subordinate to and serves the
economic construction of the country, adheres to the policy of
fewer but more professional troops according to China's actual
conditions and resolutely carries out the decision announced by
President Jiang Zemin to reduce the PLA by another 500,000
personnel.
</P>
<P>
Chi also briefed the guests on China's domestic situation, its
foreign policy and its views on current international situations.
</P>
<P>
Chumakov said that China plays an extremely important role both
in Asia and the world as a whole, and Belarus is keen to
develop close ties with China. He noted that a strong relationship
of friendship and cooperation between the two countries has been
forged, under the care of the two heads of state, and the two
countries share common understandings and stances on various
international issues.
</P>
<P>
He said it is in accord with the interests of both sides to
bolster the friendly and cooperative ties between the two armed
forces, adding he hoped that the existing friendship and
cooperation will be further strengthened.
</P>
<P>
Chi and Chumakov also exchanged views on international and
regional issues of common concern.
</P>
<P>
Chumakov arrived here May 30 on an official visit as Chi's
guest. 
</P>
</TEXT>
