<HEADLINE> China's Largest Children's Medical Center Operational </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 1 (Xinhua) -- With donations from 100 overseas
organizations, the Shanghai Children's Medical Center, the largest in
China, opened today in this east coast metropolis.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai No. 2 Medical University invested 320 million yuan
(about 39 million US dollars) in the construction of the medical
center, a gift for this year's International Children's Day for
Chinese children.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, several leading transnational companies, including
Kodak, General Electric, Hewlett-Packard and Orient Overseas
Container Line, donated a total of 31 million US dollars for the
purchase of advanced medical instruments and staff training.
</P>
<P>
The 40,000-sq-m medical center, which has 250 beds, can
accommodate an average of 1,000 patients per day. It has a full
range of departments for the treatment of children's diseases, and
will develop departments specializing in cardiovascular ailments,
emergency treatment, tumors and blood diseases. 
