<HEADLINE> Veteran Novotna Beats Teenager Kournikova </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Czech veteran Jana Novotna eliminated
teenager Anna Kournikova of Russia out of the French Open tennis
tournament here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Novotna won the delayed match 6-7, 6-3, 6-3 in over two hours
after being postponed from Sunday night when the 16-year-old
Russian trailed 2-4 in the decisive set.
</P>
<P>
When the match resumed on Monday, the Russian could do nothing
to stop the 29-year-old third seed Novotna from sailing further.
</P>
<P>
On Sunday, Spain's Arantxa Sanchez Vicario, twice a winner in
1989 and 1994, silenced another teenager American Serena Williams,
also in three sets.
</P>
<P>
In another match delayed from Sunday night, defending champion
Iva Majoli completed a three-set victory over former Wimbledon
champion Conchita Martinez of Spain 7-6, 6-7, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
Majoli will meet American second seed Lindsay Davenport in the
quarter-finals while Novotna faces American Monica Seles in a
clash of the older generation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
