<P>
KOMPONG CHAM, Cambodia, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Cambodian Prince
Norodom Ranariddh said Monday that he will called for a delay of
the coming elections if voter registration is less than 80 percent
and the access to media is not made equal.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks while traveling to the eastern province of
Kompong Cham, about 200 kilometers from Phnom Penh, to register
for the coming Assembly elections.
</P>
<P>
