FUNCINPEC and other opposition parties, have threatened to boycott
the elections.
</P>
<P>
Voter registration is from May 18 to June 15.
</P>
<P>
According to National Election Committee's (NEC) estimates, 30
percent of more of the five million eligible voters registered in
the first week.
</P>
<P>
A report in Monday's Cambodia Daily said FUNCINPEC could still
be declared ineligible for the elections if the Ministry of
Interior was to withdraw approval on grounds that FUNCINPEC still
had its own army, which is forbidden by political party law.
</P>
<P>
Troop reintegration talks between the government and the forces
loyal to Ranariddh were at a deadlock because each side accused
the other of not being serious about reintegration. 
</P>
