<HEADLINE> China to Build National Science Think Tank </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 1 (Xinhua) -- China is to construct a national
science think tank on the basis of the existing Academic
Committees of the Chinese Academy of Sciences (CAS).
</P>
<P>
"The CAS academic committees comprise the most authoritative
scientists. Therefore they should play a more active role in
helping the country," Lu Yongxiang, president of CAS, said
today at the ninth conference of CAS academicians.
</P>
<P>
"The national science think tank should be China's highest
academic assessment body," Lu said.
</P>
<P>
Scientific and technological groups are needed to join the
consultation and decision of lots of strategic and foresighted
issues concerning the country's development, Lu said.
</P>
<P>
China's many successful science promotion plans, including the
12-year development program, the science funding system and
Project 863 for high-tech enhancement, all originated from the
proposals of CAS academicians and CAS Academic Committees, Lu said.
</P>
<P>
"It's very important to introduce a scientific and democratic
system for all-round decision-making," Lu stressed.
</P>
<P>
"CAS must build the most influential consultative body for
the country's decision makers," Lu said.
</P>
<P>
The credibility and authoritativeness of CAS academicians should
be further promoted, Lu said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
