<HEADLINE> NPC Vice-Chairman Meets European Parliament Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Zou Jiahua, vice-chairman of the
Standing Committee of the National People's Congress (NPC), met
here today with a delegation from the European Parliament (EP)
specializing in relations with China.
</P>
<P>
Zou said that China and the European Union (EU) have long had
good cooperative relations. The NPC and the EP also have frequent
exchanges.
</P>
<P>
According to Zou, it is understandable for China and European
countries, whose social systems and ideology are different, to
hold different opinions on certain matters. "Through bilateral
exchanges, the two sides can seek common ground while leaving
differences aside so as to further understanding and develop
cooperation," he noted.
</P>
<P>
Per Gahrton, an EP parliamentarian and head of the delegation,
told Zou that the members of his group are representatives of six
EP parties from eight out of the 15 EU member states. They have
exchanged views with the Chinese side on economic, environmental,
global security and human rights issues. "The EU is willing to
further such ties with China," he said.
</P>
<P>
Gahrton and his party are here as guests of the NPC Standing
Committee. 
</P>
</TEXT>
