<HEADLINE> New Northeast China-Japan Air Route </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, June 1 (Xinhua) -- A MD-82 plane today left
Harbin, capital of northeast China's Heilongjiang Province, for
Niigata City in Japan, which means another regular flight linking
Northeast China and Japan has opened.
</P>
<P>
China opened flights between Shenyang, capital of Liaoning
Province in Northeast China, and Osaka, Japan, on May 19, 1998.
</P>
<P>
The once-a-week new flight is economical and convenient
for passengers, according to an official of the Shenyang-based
China Northern Airlines, which operates the flight.
</P>
<P>
The economic relationship between Heilongjiang and Japan has
made rapid progress over recent years. Statistics show that the
province's export volume to Japan reached 385 million
U.S. dollars-worth in 1997, and Japanese business people had
invested a total of 400 million U.S. dollars in Heilongjiang by
the end of last year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
