<HEADLINE> China's Policy on Comprehensive Public Security Control Hailed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 1 (Xinhua) -- China's implementation of
comprehensive management of public security is totally correct and
a fundamental solution to the law and order problems in the
country.
</P>
<P>
Luo Gan, member of the Political Bureau of the Communist Party
of China (CPC) Central Committee and of the CPC Central Committee
Secretariat, made the remark at a conference today of the Central
Committee for Comprehensive Management of Public Security.
</P>
<P>
Since 1991, when the central leadership decided to step up
comprehensive management of public security, the policy has been
well implemented throughout the country, noted Luo, who is also
chairman of the committee,
</P>
<P>
As a result, social stability has been safeguarded and the
people feel more secure, he added.
</P>
<P>
It is a crucial part of comprehensive management to crack down
on serious criminal activities that threaten public order, Luo
said, stressing that the "strike hard" principle should be
maintained, so as to keep high pressure on crime.
</P>
<P>
The authorities will give priority to combatting serious
criminal activities such as robbery, murder, causing explosions,
gangsterism, drug-related crimes and theft, according to Luo.
</P>
</TEXT>
