<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam's GDP Growth Declines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam's gross domestic product
(GDP) growth is expected to be between 6.5 percent and 6.8 percent
in the first five months of 1998, compared to 9.1 percent in the
same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Director of the Government Office Lai Van Cu said exports in
the five months increased by 10 percent to stand at 3.86 billion
U.S. dollars. The government earlier predicted the increase to be
from 25 percent to 26 percent.
</P>
<P>
The decline could be attributed to weak demand and lower
prices, reports said.
</P>
<P>
The official also said foreign direct investment in the first
five months dropped sharply, and if the situation did not improve,
investment for the whole year was expected to be only 1.8 billion
U.S. dollars, compared with 4.5 billion dollars last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
