<HEADLINE> Chinese President Urges Nurturing of More Young Scientists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin said
here today that a large number of young scientists and engineers
should be nurtured to meet the needs of science and technology
development in China and the country's modernization drive.
</P>
<P>
The key to knowledge renewal and faster development of
high-tech industries lies in fostering lots of outstanding young
people, Jiang said while meeting some academicians of the Chinese
Academy of Sciences and the Chinese Academy of Engineering, and
foreign academicians this morning.
</P>
<P>
He noted that mankind has stepped into the information age,
science and technology are developing with each passing day, and
a knowledge-based economy has taken shape. Such an economy features
unceasing renewal of knowledge and fast industrialization of new
and high technologies.
</P>
<P>
In the course of the history of science and technology, many
scientists made significant inventions when they were young.
Similarly, many statesmen and men of letters scored remarkable
achievements early in life, the president said.
</P>
<P>
"Scientific and technological development and social progress
rely on unceasing creations, which in turn rely on professionals,
especially on a steady stream of outstanding young talented
people," Jiang said.  
</P>
