<HEADLINE> Egypt Calls for International Efforts to Save </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian Foreign Minister Amr Moussa
Monday urged the international community to intensify efforts to
save the dying Mideast peace process.
</P>
<P>
"Facing up to any failure in the current bid to save the peace
process is not only an Arab responsibility but also an
international one," Moussa was quoted by Egypt's Middle East News
Agency as saying.
</P>
<P>
