should resort to in certain circumstances and when it becomes
necessary to study alternatives for immediate political action."
</P>
<P>
His words came as the Arab states are undertaking intensive
contacts for an Arab summit to unify stance among Arab countries
toward Israel's intransigence.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian-Israeli talks have been stalled since March
last year because of Israel's expansion of settlement and the
much-delayed troop redeployment in West Bank.
</P>
<P>
Citing security reasons, Israel firmly turned down a
U.S. proposal calling for Israeli troops withdrawal from 13
percent more of the West Bank.
</P>
<P>
Moussa said the ongoing consultations at various levels among
Arab states all have shown the Arab coordination in tackling the
current difficulties in the peace process.
</P>
<P>
Criticizing Israel for "wasting peace opportunities one after
another," Moussa said "a firm stance" should be taken towards
Israel's "provocative" attitude. 
