<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Sharply Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed sharply lower Monday after the
announcement by the Bank Negara (Central Bank) Friday that the
gross domestic product (GDP) declined by 1.8 percent in the first
quarter this year.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index shed 20.24
points to 518.00, the all-share Emas Index fell 4.26 points to
132.25, the Industrial Index was 21.44 points lower at 1,013.96
and the Second Board Index eased 1.64 points to 109.83.
</P>
<P>
Losers led gainers by 511 to 95 while 126 counters were
unchanged and 186 untraded.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover stood at 119.998 million shares worth
236.095 million ringgit (60.228 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The main board volume dropped to 109.369 million shares valued
at 218.973 million ringgit (55.86 million U.S. dollars) from
117.330 million shares worth 262.369 million ringgit (66.93
million U.S. dollars) last Friday.
</P>
<P>
The second board turnover stood at 10.629 million shares valued
at 17.122 million ringgit (4.367 million U.S. dollars) against
last Friday's 10.268 million shares worth 15.336 million ringgit
(3.912 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Off-market deals contracted to 1.666 million shares valued at
5.098 million ringgit (1.3 million U.S. dollars) compared with
7.841 million shares worth 13.151 million ringgit (3.354 million
U.S. dollars) on Friday.
</P>
<P>
On a sectoral basis, consumer products accounted for 6.808
million shares traded, industrial products 8.249 million shares,
construction 7.339 million shares, trading/service 26.847 million
shares, infrastructure 431,000 shares, finance 21.948 million
shares, hotels 331,000 shares, properties 14.323 million shares,
plantation 3.692 million shares, mining 509,000 shares, trusts
79,000 shares, closed/fund 10,000 shares and loans 18.803 million
shares. 
