<HEADLINE> 27 Soldiers Injured in Northern Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan government troops
conducting Operation Jaya Sikuru (Certain Victory) are facing
stiff resistance from Tamil rebels and 27 soldiers were injured in
Sunday's fighting in Northern Province, security sources said here
Monday.
</P>
<P>
The sources said the Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE)
rebels had fired mortars and artillery on the soldiers.
</P>
<P>
The government troops who commenced advancing last Wednesday
have moved more than one kilometer toward northeast of Mankulam,
the strategic town of the LTTE.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE has been waging a 15-year-old war against the
government for a separate state in the north and east of the
island.
</P>
<P>
The latest round of Operation Jaya Sikuru was launched by the
troops on May 13 last year to open a key supply line along a
highway linking Vavuniya to the Jaffna peninsula. 
</P>
