<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Academicians Conference Opens in Beijing  (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
During the five-day conference, the academicians will discuss a
series of subjects on China's economic and social development
involving water sources, knowledge-based economy, new
agro-scientific and technological revolution, urban subterranean
exploration, astronomy in the 21st century, pharmaceutical
industry based on transgenic animals and bio-pharmacies, the
modernization of traditional Chinese medicine and the development
objectives of nuclear physics in the new century and disposal of
nuclear wastes.
</P>
<P>
The academicians will also make revisions to the charters of
the two academies and elected new foreign academicians. The
Chinese Academy of Enginering will elect its president,
vice-president and members of the presidium.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Academy of Sciences and the Chinese Academy of
Engineering, set up respectively in 1949 and 1994, are China's top
scientific and technological consultance agencies and academic
thinking tank. Their research outcome represent the highest
attainment of science and technology, and engineering in the
country.
</P>
<P>
At the opening ceremony, the academicians also held a welcoming
function to 10 foreign academicians who made special trips to
Beijing for the conference.  
</P>
</TEXT>
