<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 1 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news items in
leading French newspapers on Monday:
</P>
<P>
Liberation:
</P>
<P>
-- The pilots of Air France are on strike for an undecided
period of time. Until June 4 the earliest, the company will cancel
from 75 to 90 percent of its flights. The labor conflict in Air
France is caused by a plan to reduce the pilots' salary.
</P>
