France for the recognition by the French National Assembly of the
Armenian genocide in 1915. An emergency meeting of the Turkish
Foreign Ministry Saturday planned to exert diplomatic pressure on
the French Senate not to adopt the bill passed by the National
Assembly.
</P>
<P>
Le Figaro:
</P>
<P>
-- About 100,000 passengers are stuck on their way home from
the Pentecost holiday because of a strike by the pilots of Air
France beginning Monday.
</P>
<P>
-- More than 3,000 people were killed Saturday in a violent
earthquake measuring 7.1 on the Richter scale which devastated
northeast Afghanistan and rubbed out dozens of villages from the
map. An earlier earthquake in the same region killed 4,000 in
February. 
