<HEADLINE> Zhou Gang Presents Credentials to Indian President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 1 (Xinhua) -- New Chinese Ambassador to India
Zhou Gang presented his credentials to Indian President K. R.
Narayanan here Monday and the two sides exchanged views on
furthering the friendly relations between their countries.
</P>
<P>
Zhou first conveyed President Jiang Zemin's greetings and good
wishes to the Indian president, who, in return, asked Zhou to
convey his warm greetings to President Jiang.
</P>
<P>
The Indian president recalled the long-standing friendship and
cooperation between the two great ancient nations and the Five
Principles of Peaceful Coexistence jointly worked out by the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
"Both our countries have the foresight and the wisdom to
overcome all hurdles to mutual understanding and to continue
uninterrupted our efforts to resolve our differences through
dialogue," he said. "With goodwill, mutual understanding and
appreciation of each other's interests and concerns there are no
problems between us that cannot be resolved."
</P>
<P>
He said, "During President Jiang Zemin's historic visit to
India, both sides agreed to develop a relationship of constructive
cooperation oriented toward the 21st century. Growing cooperation
in an increasing range of areas provides a new dimension to our
relations."
</P>
<P>
"These bonds do not impinge upon the interests of any country
in Asia or in the world. On the contrary we believe that they will
contribute to friendship and cooperation and peace and security in
our region and in the world," he further said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that Zhou was appointed at an important and historic
juncture in the two countries' relations. He expressed the hope
that during his tenure here, India-China relations will witness
steady improvement.
</P>
<P>
Zhou arrived here on April 22. 
</P>
</TEXT>
