<HEADLINE> Chinese FM to Attend Meeting of FMs of UNSC's Permanent Members </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Foreign Minister Tang
Jiaxuan will attend the foreign ministerial meeting of the five
permanent members of the United Nations (UN) Security Council on
June 4 in Geneva, Foreign Ministry Spokesman Zhu Bangzao announced
here today.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said the tension in South Asia caused by the nuclear tests
of India and Pakistan, as well as prevention of nuclear weapons
proliferation and other issues will be discussed in the meeting.
</P>
<P>
The convocation of this meeting was jointly proposed by China
and the United States, Zhu said, adding that Tang had discussed
matters concerning the meeting with U.S. State Secretary Madeleine
Albright over the telephone several times.
</P>
<P>
They stressed the importance of cooperation between China and
the U.S. and that among the five permanent members of the UN
Security Council in this matter, he said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the two sides believed that the five permanent
members, in accordance with the UN Charter, shouldered special
responsibility for maintaining international peace and security,
and should therefore work together to prevent the escalation of
the nuclear arms race in South Asia and restore and maintain peace
and stability in the region, Zhu noted.  
</P>
</TEXT>
