<HEADLINE> Chinese President Hails Sino-Turkish Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin,
during a meeting here today with visiting Turkish Deputy Prime
Minister Bulent Ecevit, expressed his appreciation of the positive
attitude adopted by the Turkish government towards the development
of Sino-Turkish relations.
</P>
<P>
Jiang told Ecevit that the Chinese government values its ties
with Turkey and is ready to further promote bilateral cooperation
in political, economic and other areas to serve the interests of
the two peoples as well as the peace and stability in Asia and the
world at large.
</P>
<P>
He said Sino-Turkish relations have registered a smooth
development since the two nations established diplomatic ties in
1971. The mutual understanding and bilateral economic cooperation
have been increased and expanded with frequent high-level contacts
and increased people-to-people exchanges between the two
countries, Jiang added.
</P>
<P>
Calling China "an important country in the world", Ecevit said
Turkey admires China's great progress in various fields and
appreciates China's wise foreign policy. Turkey is willing to
intensify the existing friendly and cooperative relations between
the two countries, he added.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Ecevit conveyed Jiang an invitation from
Turkish President Sulegman Demirel to visit the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
