<HEADLINE> Chinese Academicians Conference Opens in Beijing  (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 1 (Xinhua) -- A conference of the academicians of
the Chinese Academy of Sciences and of the Chinese Academy of
Engineering opened here today.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang Zemin and Premier Zhu Rongji extended their
cordial congratulations on the opening of the conference, calling
on the scientists and engineers nationwide to resolutely carry out
the strategy of revitalizing China through science and education.
</P>
<P>
More than 1,000 academicians who have come to attend the
conference will confer on major matters concerning the development
objectives for China's science and technology across the century
as well implementation of the strategy defined by the 15th
National Congress of the Communist Party of China (CPC) and the
first session of the Ninth National People's Congress (NPC).
</P>
<P>
Prior to the opening of the conference, President Jiang Zemin
met with some of the Chinese academicians of the two academies and
foreign academicians. He made remarks on the world scientific and
technological development trends and on accelerated training of
young talents in scientific sector.
</P>
<P>
Zhong Rongji, Li Lanqing, Chi Haotian, Wen Jiabao, Zhou
Guangzhao, Qian Weichang, Lu Jiaxi, Song Jian, Qian Zhengying and
Zhu Guangya were among those present at the meeting.
</P>
<P>
At the opening ceremony of the conference, Premier Zhu Rongji
delivered a two-hour report on China's present economic
situation. It is the third report concerning China's economic
situation Zhu has addressed to the academicians over the past five
years.
</P>
<P>
At a press conference of the First Session of the Ninth NPC in
the spring of this year, Premier Zhu Rongji solemnly declared to
the whole world that revitalizing China through the use of science
and technology has been listed as the prime task of his
government.
</P>
</TEXT>
