<HEADLINE> Compulsory Education Project Launched in Inner Mongolia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HOHHOT, June 1 (Xinhua) -- The State Compulsory Education
Project for Poverty-stricken Regions has been launched in north
China's Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region, according to local
government.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese central government will allocate 239 million yuan
of special fund over the next three years for carrying out the
project, the biggest "aiding the poor" educational program
in China, in the autonomous region's 51 counties and regions.
</P>
<P>
The local government will support the undertaking to the tune
of 430 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
The fund will be mainly used to improve the teaching and
management level of local high schools and elementary schools and
add teaching instruments, classroom desks and chairs as well as
library books.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the local educational departments will host a
series of training programs for primary school teachers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
