<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Powerful Bomb Explodes in Sri Lankan Tea Plantation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 1 (Xinhua) -- A powerful bomb exploded and
damaged almost an entire factory in a tea plantation in Watawala,
Central Province of Sri Lanka, Monday morning, reports reaching
here said.
</P>
<P>
A fire broke out following the explosion and was put out
immediately with the help of estate workers.
</P>
<P>
The blast occurred at dawn Monday in Watawala, about 120
kilometers from Colombo. Except for the factory watchman, the
entire 192-hectare estate at that time was deserted, the reports
said.
</P>
<P>
The explosion has caused extensive damage, especially to the
sifting room and the adjoining building.
</P>
<P>
No casualties have been reported so far, the reports said,
adding that no arrests have been made and police investigations
are under way. 
</P>
</TEXT>
