<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Foreign-funded Banks Profitable in East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Foreign-funded financial institutes
in east China's Fujian province are entering a profit-making
period, according to local government.
</P>
<P>
The province now has 26 foreign-funded financial institutes,
including 12 non-business ones.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last year, the total assets of these institutes
had reached 2.03 billion US dollars. The loans outstanding of them
was 1.16 billion US dollars while deposits standing at 823 million
US dollars.
</P>
<P>
While providing funds for the province's economic growth, these
institutes registered rapid development themselves.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, 14 business financial institutes earned profit of
20.19 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Fujian, a coastal province with developed foreign trade, used
4.2 billion US dollars of foreign funds and registered foreign
trade of 19.8 billion US dollars in 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
