<HEADLINE> Kuwait: GCC's Role Important in Gulf </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Kuwait has said the cooperation
among Gulf countries has played an important role in the region's
handling of various challenges.
</P>
<P>
In a statement commemorating the 17th anniversary of the Gulf
Cooperation Council (GCC), the Kuwaiti cabinet said the
organization has satisfactorily brought the countries together in
meeting challenges.
</P>
<P>
Citing an example, the statement which is available Monday said
the GCC members were united against Iraq's aggression of Kuwait in
1990, contributing to the liberation.
</P>
<P>
The cabinet also expressed the confidence that the GCC will
continue to strengthen solidarity among its member states and
peoples.
</P>
<P>
GCC, an economic, political and defense alliance, was founded on
May 25, 1981. It groups Bahrain, Kuwait, Oman, Qatar, Saudi
Arabia, and the United Arab Emirates.
</P>
<P>
A GCC Secretariat report issued to marking the anniversary
report also highlighted the organization's vital role in
maintaining well-established relations among member states.
</P>
<P>
The council held a distinguished and united position among
Arab, Islamic and international organizations and forums including
the United Nations organization, the report said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
