<DOCNO> XIE19980601.0138 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Complaint Phone Greatly Helps Shenyang People </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Common people in Shenyang,
northeast China's Liaoning Province, can turn to a complaint phone
call for help when they are in difficulties.
</P>
<P>
China's first complaint center, established late January in the
industrial city, has helped solve problems on water, electricity
and gas supply, environmental protection and others for local
residents, according to center's officials.
</P>
<P>
In the first three months of operation, the complaint center
dealt with more than 30,000 complaints. A retired government
official had fretted about the housing problem for over 10
years. After he tried to dial 2211, or the special complaint phone
number, his problem was handled properly by relative official
departments.
</P>
<P>
Complaints collected by the center have also helped City Mayor
of Shenyang Mu Suixin know better about conditions of the people
and public feelings. He said that the complaint phone is a good
helper for him to run the city and understand what is going on
among the people.
</P>
<P>
All the complaints have been recorded in particular
computers. Then the center urges official departments to handle
them within a limited period.
</P>
<P>
Many residents said that the city authorities care much more
about their daily life.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Shenyang has set up a complaint network, which
connects district and county governments, and official departments
in charge of urban utilities.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
