<HEADLINE> Hu Jintao Meets with Representatives of Children </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 1 (Xinhua) -- On the International Children's
Day, senior Chinese leaders Hu Jintao and Li Lanqing here today
met with representatives of children and social workers on
children and had a photo taken with them.
</P>
<P>
Hu Jintao, Standing Committee member of the Political Bureau of
the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee and
vice-president of China, extended warm regards to the children and
hard-working teachers across the country.
</P>
<P>
Being the trans-century generation, the current children will
shoulder the historic task of modernizing the country and
revitalizing the Chinese nation, Hu said.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his hope that the children nurture lofty ideals
and fine virtue, lay a good foundation of knowledge and make
physical exercises so as to contribute more to the motherland in
the future.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the entire society should also show care for the
children and create a good social environment for their healthy
growth. 
</P>
</TEXT>
