<HEADLINE> 11 Kurdish Rebels Killed in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Eleven members of the outlawed
Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) were killed in clashes with
government security forces in southeastern Turkey Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Newspaper and radio reports said Monday that 10 militants were
killed in clashes in Cevre village in Hakkari province and another
one in Sirnak province. Both provinces border northern Iraq.
</P>
<P>
One soldier was also reportedly killed in the clashes.
</P>
<P>
The PKK has been fighting a separatist war for autonomy in
southeastern Turkey since 1984, which has claimed over 35,000
lives. 
</P>
</TEXT>
