<HEADLINE> China's Two Oil Groups To Grow Larger </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, June 1 (Xinhua) -- China has decided to enlarge its
two leading oil groups by adding designated number of local
petroleum companies and fueling stations to each of them.
</P>
<P>
The information is learned from a signing ceremony here
recently on China National Petroleum Corporation's (CNPC) control
of all oil companies in Sichuan Province.
</P>
<P>
The move is considered as a major reform measure to adjust
industrial structure, streamline petroleum management system and
improve petroleum circulation.
</P>
<P>
According to the reform plan, which has been approved by the
State Council, CNPC and China National Petrochemical Corporation
(SINOPEC) will control all oil and gas fields, oil refineries and
petrochemical enterprises, and fuelling stations in the country.
</P>
<P>
CNPC will focus on exploration and production of oil and gas,
whereas SINOPEC will prioritize the production of petrochemicals.
</P>
<P>
In line with the reform plan, the State and Chemical Industry
Bureau under the State Economic and Trade Commission (SETC) has
been set up.
</P>
<P>
Experts predict that the two giant oil enterprise groups will
enter the ranks of the world's top 500 companies in terms of sales
revenue.
</P>
<P>
Under the reform plan, concerned provinces, municipalities,
autonomous regions, as well as cities enjoying an
independent-budget status are urged to cooperate closely with CNPC
or SINOPEC and finish all handover affairs before June 30.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
