<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fujian to Extend Fishing Ban </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, June 1 (Xinhua) -- East China's Fujian province has
decided to extend its fishing moratorium period from two months
to three months this year to preserve marine resources.
</P>
<P>
The moratorium area will also be expanded, according to the
provincial fishery department.
</P>
<P>
Trawlers and net catches by sailboats will be prohibited from
June 16 to September 15 in the area to the north of 26 degrees
north latitude, according to department officials.
</P>
<P>
Similar bans will also be adopted from June 16 to August 15 in
the area from 26 degrees north latitude to 24 degrees 30 minutes
north latitude.
</P>
<P>
China has adopted such a ban for three years and registered good
results. 
</P>
</TEXT>
