<HEADLINE> 12 Killed as Mini-bus, Taxis Collide in S. Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Twelve people were killed and
21 injured when two mini-bus taxis collided head-on near
Bloemfontein in central South Africa on Sunday evening.
</P>
<P>
South African Press Association (SAPA) Monday quoted a
provincial police spokesman as saying that the dead included a
two-month-old baby and two teenagers. Both taxi drivers were
killed in the crash.
</P>
<P>
The collision occurred at 5.45 p.m. (1545 GMT) about 27
kilometers outside Bloemfontein, South Africa's judicial capital.
</P>
<P>
The two taxis were travelingin opposite directions to and
from Bloemfontein.
</P>
<P>
Sunday's accident followed two horror crashes on Saturday
morning.
</P>
<P>
Eighteen people were killed and dozens injured when 10 cars
piled up on the N1 highway near Johannesburg Saturday. Another
crash in Kwazulu-Natal claimed 10 lives when a bus carrying 30
passengers overturned.
</P>
<P>
In a separate accident in Kwazulu-Natal Saturday afternoon,
three people were killed and 15 injured when an army truck and a
light delivery vehicle collided. 
</P>
</TEXT>
