<HEADLINE> Shanghai Sets up Exhibition Center of Listed Companies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 1 (Xinhua) -- A exhibition center of listed
companies has been put into operation in the Pudong New Area of
Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The center, which is located at the Lujiazui Financial and
Trade Zone, is mainly established by the newspaper of Shanghai
Securities, to help the listed companies improve their public
images and have access to business information.
</P>
<P>
China has currently had 800 listed companies. With the rapid
development of the country's securities market, the establishment
of such a service center may be fairly useful, according to local
experts.
</P>
<P>
"We will move some of our major departments into the center, in
a bid to provide better services for the listed companies," said
Wang Yuchun, general manager of the Shanghai Shenying Wanguo
Security Co. Ltd.
</P>
<P>
So far, deputies of 14 listed companies have inspected the
newly-built exhibition center.  
</P>
</TEXT>
