<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Illegal Foreign Falcon Hunters Punished in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, June 1 (Xinhua) -- The police in northwest China's
Gansu province has punished nearly 1,000 foreigners who
broke Chinese laws to catch China-protected falcons.
</P>
<P>
An official with the provincial public security department
attributed the large number of foreign illegal hunters to the
rising price for falcons in the international market.
</P>
<P>
Falcons are pets of overseas millionaires, since they can guard
houses and property, search for mines, and deliver messages.
</P>
<P>
Over the past few years, many Pakistanis, who came to China
in the name of tourists, catched and purchased a great number of
falcons in the Hexi Corridor in Gansu.
</P>
<P>
According to Chinese laws, local policemen recently confiscated
their hunting tools and gave them fine penalties. Some involving
in crimes have even been arrested. 
</P>
</TEXT>
