<HEADLINE> East China City to Support Agricultural Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Xiaoshan city in east China's
Zhejiang province recently adopted preferential policies to
support foreigners to invest in agricultural projects.
</P>
<P>
Foreigners investing in agricultural projects for 15 years or
more will receive special treatment in respect of tax and land
policies, noted local government.
</P>
<P>
The tax policies include three years of remission of
agricultural taxes and that levies on agricultural special
product. The income tax for the firms will also be remitted in the
first two profiting years and cut to some extent in the following
years.
</P>
<P>
Foreigners to invest in agricultural development projects will
enjoy longer operation rights on land and enterprises, according
to the policies.  
</P>
</TEXT>
