<HEADLINE> Guangdong Standardizes Road Toll Charging </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Guangdong Province recently
issued regulations concerning toll road management.
</P>
<P>
Under the new rules, only roads constructed with the approval
of the provincial government are entitled to charge tolls after
completion. And all unauthorized roads do not have the right to
charge tolls.
</P>
<P>
The roads that have already paid back bank loan principal and
interest are no longer entitled to charge fees. A prolongation
requires special approval of the provincial government. 
</P>
</TEXT>
