<HEADLINE> Shanghai Charity Fund Helps 50,000 Needy Families </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 1 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Charity Fund has
helped more than needy 50,000 families since it was set up four
year ago, according to sources with the fund.
</P>
<P>
Over the past four years, the fund has raised 166 million yuan
(20 million US dollars) and spent a total of 59 million yuan (7.1
million US dollars) on charity projects for the elderly people,
poor students and families in need.
</P>
<P>
More than eight million yuan (964,000 US dollars) has been
spent on education and training programs, by establishing 13
training bases around the city and 25 kinds of professional
training courses.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, some 10,000 laid-off factory workers have been
re-trained and half of them have found new jobs. Approximately
3,000 poor students have received grant-in-aid from the charity
fund.
</P>
<P>
With the help of the fund, 80 orphanized children in Shanghai
have found their "temporary homes" with local families, while 31
others have been adopted by foster parents.
</P>
<P>
Furthermore, the Zhongren Apartment for the elderlies which has
just been completed with some 88 million yuan (10.6 million US
dollars) from the fund, along with a nearby recreation center
built one year earlier, will become the largest housing project of
its kind for the senior citizens in the municipality.
</P>
<P>
The fund is expected to train another 10,000 factory lay-off
workers by the end of May next year and assist additional 10,000
needy families before the Spring Festival sets in early next year,
according to a person in charge of the fund. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
