<HEADLINE> City Lists Projects For Overseas Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Fuzhou, capital of east China's
Fujian Province, has listed 80 local state-owned companies for
overseas investment totaling 1.05 billion U.S. dollars this year.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, the city has successfully relieved over 200
state firms from loss-making by using foreign investment.
</P>
<P>
These state companies are attractive to investors for their
sound infrastructure and skillful workers, and thus, they are
easily to begin new operations only by upgrading part of the
equipment, according to some local observers.
</P>
<P>
In related developments, more than 100 small state firms are
looking for foreign buyers or leasers. Overseas investors are
allowed to join public biddings without any pre-conditions.
</P>
<P>
Foreign buyers are only required to buy the factory buildings
or equipment, while the redundant-staff of these firms will be
re-employed under the government re-employment program. 
