<HEADLINE> Exports on Rise in Central China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, June 1 (Xinhua) -- The value of exports in central
China's Henan Province is expected to rise by 10 percent this year
from some 2.23 billion US dollars last year.
</P>
<P>
Since 1991 local exports grew at an average of 13.6 percent in
the province.
</P>
<P>
Besides general and traditional commodities, Henan will add to
its export list completed equipment as well as machinery and
electronics products, which are expected to contribute over 25
percent of local exports by the turn of the century.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the export of textiles, light industrial goods and
farm and sideline produce will also be on rise.
</P>
<P>
Henan province now boasts more than 300 enterprises with rights
to manage export trade and will strive to develop 30 exporters
each earning over 10 million US dollars in foreign exchange every
year.
</P>
<P>
Nevertheless, local exports in the first four months of this
year went down slightly from the same period in 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
