items in leading Israeli newspapers Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Jerusalem Post
</P>
<P>
-- Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu is expected to
propose a staged and conditional pullback from up to 15 percent of
the West Bank at a weekly cabinet meeting Monday.
</P>
<P>
Netanyahu is acting under an unofficial deadline set by United
States Secretary of State Madeleine Albright, which requires
Israel submit its ultimate redeployment plan to Washington by the
end of this week.
</P>
