<BODY>
<HEADLINE> North China City Using More Overseas Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, June 1 (Xinhua) -- The inflow of overseas
investment in Shijiazhuang, capital of north China's Hebei
Province, has grown at an annual rate of 50 percent since 1993 and
hit 502 million US dollars early this year.
</P>
<P>
The city set up its first overseas-funded enterprise in 1980
and the number of operational overseas-funded businesses reached
533 early this year. Last year, these enterprises generated 180
million US dollars in foreign exchange from exports and earned 654
million yuan in profits.
</P>
<P>
During recent years, the overseas investment has been mainly
used to reform the state-owned enterprises and upgrade their
products.
</P>
<P>
Shijiazhuang has trade contracts with over 100 countries and
regions, and the number of transnationals having investment in
the city has exceeded 20. 
</P>
</TEXT>
