<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Spain Wins European Under-21 Soccer Crown </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Spain claimed the European
Under-21 Soccer Championship on Sunday, edging Greece 1-0 in the
final with a bizarre goal in the 65th minute.
</P>
<P>
Greece created several scoring opportunities during the whole
match but failed to change the point.
</P>
<P>
Spain snatched the chance when Ivan Perez headed home a bizarre
goal in the 65th, scoring on a stray corner kick by Juan Carlos
Valderon which slipped through the hands of Greek goalkeeper
Dimitrios Eleftheropoulos.
</P>
<P>
Greece missed a chance to equalize in the 81st minute when
Vasileios Lakis found himself alone in front of Arnau but overshot
the goal from point-blank range.
</P>
<P>
It's the second championship title for the Spanish, who beat
Italy in the 1986 final on penalty kicks.
</P>
<P>
In the match for bronze, Steffen Iversen scored twice as Norway
downed the Netherlands 2-0.
</P>
<P>
Norway opened the scoring in the 17th minute on a rebound,
kicked in by Iversen after Dutch goalkeeper Jim van Fessem cleared
Andreas Lund's low shot from six meters.
</P>
<P>
Iversen made it 2-0 in the 74th minute with a superb lob over
Van Fessem from eight meters. 
</P>
</TEXT>
