<HEADLINE> China to Issue Commemorative Coins for Rare Animals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 1 (Xinhua) -- The People's Bank of China, the
nation's central bank, will issue two sets of commemorative coins
featuring two rare wild animals on June 2.
</P>
<P>
The scheduled issue includes six million coins featuring the
crested ibis and another six million coins featuring the
red-crowned crane. Both coins have a face value of five yuan and a
diameter of 32mm.
</P>
<P>
The coins, minted in red-copper alloy, will be circulated at
its par value, the central bank said in an announcement.  
</P>
</TEXT>
