<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guangxi Speeds up Communication Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Guangxi Zhang Autonomous Region, a
multi-ethnic area in south China, is to invest 6.8 billion yuan in
building a land-air-sea communication system this year, 1.5
billion yuan more than the planned figure.
</P>
<P>
Of the total investment, 1.7 billion yuan will be used to
complete two sections on the expressway between Guilin and Beihai
cities. Meanwhile, construction on a highway linking Nanning, the
regional capital, with Baise, a ring-road in Guilin which is a
scenic spot, and a highway between Wuzhou and Xindu will be
accelerated.
</P>
<P>
Some 900 million yuan of investment will be channeled to build
the second phase of Xijiang water course, two new berths at
Fangchenggang Port and the third phase of Beihai Port.
</P>
<P>
An expansion Project at Beihai Airport will cost an investment
of 250 million yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
