<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tianjin to Invest Heavily in Infrastructure This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, June 1 (Xinhua) -- North China's Tianjin Municipality
will spend 4.2 billion yuan in building 52 infrastructural
projects in its New Coastal Area this year.
</P>
<P>
The information is learned from the on-going First Session of
the 13th Tianjin Municipal People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
According to the session, the projects will include the Tianjin
section of the Shanhaiguan Pass-Guangzhou Expressway, three
bridges and two flyovers, eight berths at Tianjin Port, expansion
of Tianjin International Coastal Airport, as well as development
of some new air routes.
</P>
<P>
The New Coastal Area of Tianjin has an area of 350 sq km,
including a development zone, a bonded zone and the Tianjin
Port.
</P>
<P>
The area has grown into the most dynamic region in economic
development in Tianjin through four years' construction. Its
gross domestic product (GDP) now makes up 30.8 percent of the
municipality's total, while its exports account for 48.5 percent
of Tianjin's total.
</P>
<P>
The area has formed electronic, food, metallurgical, chemical
industrial sectors and become the best destination of
investment for the processing industry in China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
