<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Residents Invest in Treasury Bonds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Residents of this largest economic
and financial center of China have developed great interest in
buying state treasury bonds, official figures indicate.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai residents purchased a total of more than 15.38 billion
yuan (1.85 billion US dollars) in certificate treasury bonds
between February 20 and May 20, about 95.3 percent of the total
value of government bonds to be sold in the city, according to
statistics of the Shanghai branch of the People's Bank of China,
the central bank.
</P>
<P>
Bank sources said that state treasury bonds have become a
preferred investment choice of Shanghai residents, who have been
known as wise in money matters.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Ministry of Finance has announced the issue of
137.36 billion yuan (16.55 billion US dollars) in certificate
treasury bonds this year, which is on offer through October 31.
</P>
<P>
As prices and interest rates on bank savings deposits keep
going down, more Chinese residents have been turning to treasury
bonds as their main investment option. China has cut bank interest
rates four times since May 1996, with the latest on March 25.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
