<HEADLINE> South Korean Student Movement Members to be Arrested </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, June 1 (Xinhua) -- South Korean National Police Agency
Monday decided to arrest members of the Federation of Korean
University Student Councils, or Hanchongnyon, on charge of
violating national security law.
</P>
<P>
Of the total 1,100 Hanchongnyon members, 675 participated in
the election for the group's leadership by casting ballots last
Friday through the Internet despite repeated warnings from the
police against such practice.
</P>
<P>
Hanchongnyon, which declared that the South Korean government
should be overthrown for being the "puppet of the regime of U.S.
imperialists," conducted its sixth election of leadership and held
a demonstration in downtown Seoul last Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Police have confirmed the names of 128 students and put them on
a wanted list across the nation, the Yonhap News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
So far, police have released most of the 562 detained
Hanchongnyon members who attended the group's new leadership
inauguration and held a May-30 demonstration in downtown Seoul.
</P>
</TEXT>
