<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Asia Oil &AMP; Gas Conference Opens in Malaysia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 1 (Xinhua) -- The Third Asia Oil and Gas
Conference opened here Monday to deliberate the impact of the
Asian economic turmoil and political issues and forge and enhance
relationships.
</P>
<P>
Officiating at the two-day conference, Malaysian Deputy Prime
Minister Anwar Ibrahim said the economic crisis in East Asia calls
for a fundamental re-think about many of long-held assumptions in
the region and poses a challenge to the region's capacity to cope
with globalization.
</P>
<P>
He said, "This is not to deny the region's achievements in the
past decade, especially in the socio-economic field, and there is
no reason to doubt that East Asia can rise again in the future
provided we seize the moment to institute long-delayed reforms
that would rid our economic and political systems of excesses and
abuses."
</P>
<P>
The immediate challenge is in finding the best way to restore
investor confidence in the region, he said, calling for the region
to act as one in resolving the crisis and warning slow recovery in
one country would drag down others and indeed the region.
</P>
<P>
"One lesson that we can draw upon from this crisis is that we
are closely interlinked and interdependent. Thus it is imperative
that we work together in revitalizing regional economies," Anwar
stressed.
</P>
<P>
On Asia's oil and gas industry, Anwar said the industry
benefited tremendously from the region's rapid growth during the
last decade and the future is still promising as Asian energy
demand, despite the crisis, is expected to remain robust.
</P>
<P>
He said that according to the World Bank, the Asia-Pacific
region's energy demand is likely to exceed one third of the global
total by the year 2010. Hence, the biggest challenge facing the
energy industry in the Asia-Pacific region, particularly in the
oil and gas industry, lies in meeting Asia's seemingly insatiable
appetite for energy.
</P>
<P>
Some 600 participants from 28 countries and regions are
attending the conference. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
