<HEADLINE> Mahathir Leaves on Working Visit to Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Malaysian Prime Minister
Mahathir Mohamad left here Monday for a five-day working visit to
Japan to speak at two major conferences on East Asian economies
and the future of Asia.
</P>
<P>
Mahathir is scheduled to deliver a keynote address on
"Revitalization of the Japanese and East Asian Economies" in Tokyo
Tuesday at the fifth symposium of the Institute for International
Monetary Affairs, which is an affiliate of the International
Monetary Fund (IMF).
</P>
<P>
Participants in the symposium comprise ministers and top
corporate leaders.
</P>
<P>
Mahathir is also expected to address the Nikkei Conference
Thursday which is themed "Future of Asia."
</P>
<P>
The conference is held annually since 1995 and is aimed at
deepening understanding between Japan and other Asian nations.
</P>
<P>
Mahathir will return home Friday. 
