<HEADLINE> Montenegro Begins Parliamentary Elections </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Voters began voting a new
parliament in Montenegro Sunday, the Tanjug News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
By 06:00 pm local time, about 60 to 80 percent of 420,000
registered voters had turned up for the elections.
</P>
<P>
A total of 709 candidates from 15 political parties and
coalitions are competing for the 78 parliamentary seats.
</P>
<P>
Preliminary results are expected early Tuesday, according to
the electoral commission.
</P>
<P>
Commission representatives and international observers said the
elections were held in an atmosphere of just and democracy.
</P>
