<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dozens Killed in Latest Conflict in Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, May 31 (Xinhua) -- At least four Yugoslav frontier
guards and policemen as well as dozens of ethnic Albanian
militants were killed in the latest conflict on Saturday through
Sunday in the troubled Kosovo province of Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
The official Tanjug news agency said that in Drenica, a village
to the west of Pristina, the provincial capital, a Serbian
policeman was killed Sunday in an ambush. In a similar attack in
the border town of Deccani on Sunday morning, three others were
wounded, one seriously.
</P>
<P>
Also on Sunday, Serbian policemen killed dozens of armed ethnic
Albanians when they traded fire in the village of Vranovac, the
Tanjug said.
</P>
<P>
It added that on Saturday, three Yugoslav frontier soldiers
were killed on their border post at Morina near Djakovica, two
others wounded. In return, 11 ethnic Albanian militants were under
arrest.
</P>
<P>
Tensions in Kosovo escalated in early March this year, when
four policemen and 16 Albanians were killed in an armed conflict.
</P>
<P>
Ethnic Albanians, accounting for 90 percent of the population
in Kosovo, have been seeking independence from Yugoslavia since
1981. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
