<HEADLINE> Russia: Financial Market to Return to Normal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 1(Xinhua) -- The Russian financial market can be
expected to return to normal next week, Russian Minister of
Economy said Sunday.
</P>
<P>
By the end of this year or early next year, he added, the
rediscount rate would be reduced to 20 to 25 percent, the level of
September of 1997, Yakov Urinson said in a local TV program.
</P>
<P>
Russia's large reserves of gold and foreign currencies are
guarantee of a stable ruble, said the minister, asking the
Russians not to change rubles into U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Also Urinson reiterated the importance of a sound and
smooth tax-collection, calling it a major stabilizing factor.
</P>
