<HEADLINE> United States Beat Spain to Keep Winning Streak </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BREMEN, Germany, May 31 (Xinhua) -- The United States overcame
early setbacks to beat Spain 79-68 Sunday night, keeping their
winning streak at the Women's World Basketball Championship.
</P>
<P>
Lisa Leslie topped the team by getting a game-high 21 points
and 12 rebounds. The WNBA star was helped by Natalie Williams' 13
and Champiqu Holdsclaw's 11.
</P>
<P>
The Americans, the Atlanta Olympic gold medalists, met a strong
challenge in the first half and trailed 7-13 before they bursted
with a 13-2 run to regain the lead at 20-15.
</P>
<P>
The first half ended with the United States leading 36-33.
</P>
<P>
The Americans opened the second half with a 9-0 run and
extented the lead to 45-33.
</P>
<P>
Ana Belenavaro scored 16 points for Spain, which had a 3-2
record in the team standings. Rosanra Sandchez added 12.  
