<HEADLINE> Palomino to Retire from Boxing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Former world welterweight
champion Carlos Palomino wants to retire after losing a 10-round
decision to Wilfredo Rivera of Puerto Rico last night at Los
Angleles.
</P>
<P>
"I gave it all I had. I will now concentrate on my acting
career," said Palomino, 48, who fought for the first time since
Oct. 26, 1997. He ends his career at 31-4-3 with 19 knockouts.
</P>
<P>
Palomino retired for the first time in 1979, on his 30th
birthday. He won the WBC welterweight title in 1976 and held it
unitl losing to Wilfredo Benitez three years later. 
</P>
