<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia Keep Unbeaten, Trounce Japan at Basketball Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BREMEN, Germany, May 30 (Xinhua) -- Russia built a 5-0 record
after trouncing Asian runners-up Japan 103-76 on Sunday in the
second run of the Women's World Basketball Championship.
</P>
<P>
WNBA star Elena Nikonova tossed in a game-high 19 points and
nine rebounds and guard Nadeja Mrilova added 18 for Russia, which
will meet the United States Monday for the winner of group E.
</P>
<P>
Pre-game favorite Russia met little challenge and took a 50-36
halftime lead and then enlarged their advantage to as many as 30
points at 83-53 on Mrilov's lay-up with 8:48 to play.
</P>
<P>
Japan, which used accurate three-pointers to beat Lithuania and
placed second in the preliminary group, scored eight
three-pointers against Russia's four but had only 30 percentage
(8-23).
</P>
<P>
Akemi Okazato came off the bench to lead the Japanese with 20
points including six three-points. She was followed by Kumiko
Yamada, also off the bench, with 10 points.
</P>
<P>
WNBA player Mikiko Hagiwra scored nine points in her 25 minutes
play for Japan, which will face China on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Spain take on the United States, which also kept an unbeaten
book, late Sunday night. 
</P>
</TEXT>
